&lt;GKN Plc> said it and &lt;ZahnradfabrikFriedrichshafen AG> would reorganise the ownership structure oftheir &lt;Viscodrive GmbH> joint venture.    Under the agreement, GKN's Uni-Cardan AG unit wouldincrease its stake in Viscodrive to 75 pct from 50 pct, whileZF's stake would drop to 25 pct.     At the same time ZF would take an 80 pct stake in a newcompany, &lt;Steertec Lenkungen GmbH> leaving Uni-Cardan with 20pct.    Viscodrive manufactures viscous control units whileSteertec will develop power steering systems. REUTER&#3;